# Production — set ONE strategy (then rebuild the frontend):

# (1) API on the SAME host as this site under /api (reverse proxy). Fixes "web page" errors on upload:
# REACT_APP_SAME_ORIGIN_API=1

# (2) OR point to your Node API explicitly (must reach JSON, not index.html):
# REACT_APP_API_URL=https://your-backend-project.vercel.app/api

# Optional: if REACT_APP_API_URL is missing at build, split-deploy fallback (must end with /api)
# REACT_APP_API_FALLBACK_URL=https://your-backend-project.vercel.app/api

# Local CRA dev: proxy /api/quotes → ships server (default http://127.0.0.1:3001). Set to 0 to disable ships proxy.
# REACT_APP_SHIPS_API_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:3001
#
# Zippyyy Ships Express API — REQUIRED on this Vercel (storefront) project for /api/quotes to work.
# Value = URL of the Node ships server where EASYSHIP_API_KEY is set (can be another Vercel/Railway URL).
# No trailing slash. Example: https://zippyyy-ships-api.vercel.app
# SHIPS_API_BASE=https://your-zippyyy-ships-server.example.com
#
# Note: EASYSHIP_API_KEY must be on the SHIPS server project, not only here. Test: GET https://yoursite.com/api/health → easyshipConfigured: true
